README for GitSync
  A simple and small script to sync your local git repo with your remote repo
Installation
  sudo cp gs /usr/bin
Usage
  *Note: You should have already installed 'git' and git repo
  If you are already in your local repo, just execute 'gs' and wait to calculate files ad enter your username and password.  
  If you are in another directory and want to syncyour git just execute 'gs' followed by your loal git directory.

Taken from https://culturedcode.com/things/wiki/index.php/Syncing_Things_with_git_and_Launchd and modified by me :)
